Gauteng’s crime-fighting initiatives have been given a boost. JOHANNESBURG - Gauteng’s crime-fighting initiatives have been given a boost. Fifty-five new-high performance vehicles have been handed over to the province by Police Minister Bheki Cele. The cars will be used to tackle aggravated robbery, among other crimes. READ: Police need to wage war on GBV: Cele Police hope the high-performance cars will give criminals a run for their money. The province has seen a spike in cases of aggravated robbery in recent years, with armed robberies, truck hijackings, and cash-in-transit heists being big concerns and authorities are hoping to turn the tide. eNCA's Manqoba Mchunu shares more details in the video above.